decks.notes: The deck focuses on assembling the Doomsday combo, which involves using Doomsday to stack the top five cards of the library in a specific order to win the game. The deck includes various tutors, cantrips, and counterspells to help find and protect the combo pieces. It also includes cards like Necropotence and Thassa's Oracle to help with card advantage and alternate win conditions. The goal is to quickly and efficiently set up the Doomsday pile while disrupting the opponent's game plan with counterspells.

The deck revolves around using artifacts like Mana Vault, Mana Crypt, and Mishra's Workshop to generate a lot of mana quickly. It also includes cards like Paradoxical Outcome and Tinker to combo off and either draw a huge amount of cards or search for key artifacts like Time Vault. The goal is to assemble the Time Vault and Voltaic Key combo to take extra turns and eventually win the game. Cards like Force of Will and Coveted Jewel provide additional protection and value. The deck focuses on efficient mana generation and powerful artifact synergies to outpace the opponent.

The primary strategy of this deck is to control the game through a combination of powerful spells, fast mana acceleration, and disruptive creatures. The goal is to outvalue and outmaneuver the opponent by utilizing cards like Ancestral Recall, Time Walk, and powerful artifacts like Tolarian Academy and Time Vault. The deck also includes powerful tutors like Demonic Tutor and Vampiric Tutor to find key pieces while using counterspells like Force of Will and Flusterstorm to protect the game plan. With access to a wide range of versatile cards, this deck aims to dominate the opponent through resource denial and incremental advantages.

The deck focuses on generating massive card advantage and mana through its synergy with artifacts and spells like Paradoxical Outcome. It aims to quickly assemble a combo involving Time Vault and Voltaic Key to take extra turns and secure victory. The deck also utilizes counter magic and card draw to control the game and protect its key pieces. With Lurrus of the Dream-Den as a companion, the deck can continually recur important cards from the graveyard, ensuring its strategy remains consistent and powerful throughout the match.

The deck focuses on disrupting the opponent's game plan by playing hatebear creatures like Anointed Peacekeeper and Archon of Emeria, while also utilizing disruptive spells like Chancellor of the Annex and Trinisphere. It also aims to control the opponent's resources with cards like Wasteland and Strip Mine, and uses mana acceleration from cards like Ancient Tomb and the Moxen to quickly play out threats. The deck's strategy is to apply pressure while hindering the opponent's ability to cast spells efficiently, ultimately overwhelming them with creatures and disruption.
